table.name: Boost pressure base map (Engine Speed, Injection Quantity)
table.description: Base map for boost pressure P_boost = f(Engine Speed, Injection Quantity). This map provides the set value for boost which is the base for having more air mass to change the lambda and somkebehaviour of the engine. Map uses common axis, so be careful when changing them, it will have an affect to a lot of other maps !

table.name: Upper Limit of Pilot control #1 (Engine Speed)
table.description: Pilot control of the boost pressure control valve PWM = f(Engine Speed, Injection Quantity). Pilot control is a controlled add on value for boost value control. Changing set value of boost request will need a change of the control map two, if the control should not be very spiky. It also has an influence to the response of the boost when changing from low to high boost requests. Map uses common axis, so be careful when changing them, it will have an affect to a lot of other maps !

table.name: Coolant dep. Injection Quantity limiter (Vehicle Speed, Coolant Temp)
table.description: Coolant dependent Injection Quantity Limiter: IQ = f(Vehicle Speed,T_coolant), This map can be used to reduce IQ ( -> torque) depending on actual coolant temperature and vehicle speed. This maps is an overheating protection

table.name: Railpressure dep. Injection Quantity limiter (Engine Speed, Railpressure)
table.description: Railpressure dependent Injection Quantity Limiter: IQ = f(Engine Speed, Railpressure), This map can be used to reduce IQ ( -> torque) depending on actual railpressure. Smokebehaviour is getting less, when railpressure drops, so there is an direct influence of rail pressure and smoke behaviour. This map got the same duty as the somke limiter maps.

table.name: overboost dep. Injection Quantity limiter (Engine Speed, charge air pressure)
table.description: Overboost dependent Injection Quantity Limiter: IQ = f(Engine Speed,P_charge air pres), This map is used to reduce IQ ( -> torque) depending on actual overboost while too mutch boost depention on spiking or failure. This maps is an protection of the charge air control and turbo charger. It must set up, if you rise the boost.

table.name: Charge air temp dep. Injection Quantity limiter (Engine Speed, charge air temp)
table.description: Charge air temp dependent Injection Quantity Limiter: IQ = f(Engine Speed,P_charge air pres), This map is used to reduce IQ ( -> torque) depending on actual charge air temperature. This maps is an protection of the charge air control and turbo charger

air mass dep. smoke limiter (1) (Engine Speed, air mass)
table.description: This map limits injection quantity depending on air mass: IQ = f(Engine Speed, air mass). It is called "somke limiter" because it has a direct influence to the smoke behaviour of the engine. To get an direction how to treat this map, calculate Lambda of the map (Lambda = Air mass / IQ /14,7). The lower lambda is, the more smokey the engine will be. Another point: effectivity of the air mass system is getting lower with raising engine speed ( -> effec. of the turbo charger). Because of this, IQ has to fall at same air mass and raising enginespeed. Be carefull with this map ! DPF cannot handle a lot of smoke ! .
